  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Sequential input of word embeddings into RNN may express local dependencies and sentence structures.",
    "However, in LSTM, sequential input of word representations can result in the weight of the words at the beginning of the sentence being greater than the weight of the words at the end.",
    "To change the semantic contribution of the beginning and end of the sentence, ELMo introduces the bidirectional LSTM based on the attention mechanism.",
    "Thus, the effect of EMLo is better than LSTM.Many algorithms based on the text representation are mainly expanded from word2vec.",
    "Many of the existing works of the text embedding focused simply on the word representation as the input system [8,14]."
  ],
